com.yahoo.bullet.storm.drpc.utils

Class DRPCOutputCollector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yahoo.bullet.storm.drpc.utils.DRPCOutputCollector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.storm.spout.ISpoutOutputCollector, org.apache.storm.task.IErrorReporter, org.apache.storm.task.IOutputCollector

    public class DRPCOutputCollector
extends Object
implements org.apache.storm.spout.ISpoutOutputCollector, org.apache.storm.task.IOutputCollector
    This class can be used as a collector for spouts and bolts that do not actually emit. This is used to control the DRPCSpout spout and ReturnResults bolt classes to not actually do the emit. ReturnResults does not need to emit but can call ack or fail DRPCSpout only needs the emit.

      • reset

        public List<List<Object>> reset()
        Returns and resets the last series of tuples emitted to this collector. This method is not idempotent. It resets this collector state if there were any tuples to emit. Further calls will not return the tuples. They return null.
        Returns:
        The List of tuples emitted since the last call to this method.

      • haveOutput

        public boolean haveOutput()
